# Flux Deal Orchestrator (Canonical Ops)

## System Boundaries (CRITICAL — Read First)
Load `config/flow-ownership.json` before ANY action.

| System | Owns | Cursor NEVER Does |
|--------|------|-------------------|
| **Comet Browser** | GHL UI, fallback browser scrape | B2B lead gen (Cursor deal-hunter owns) |
| **GHL** | Customer SMS/email, trials, nurture, stage-triggered workflows | Customer workflow enrollment via Zapier |
| **Website** | Stripe checkout, monthly billing | Duplicate payment links |
| **Perplexity** | Research, scoring, outreach copy | Re-score or regenerate copy |
| **Cursor** | **B2B lead gen (deal-hunter)**, audit, gap-fill, stage sync, Stripe verify, Slack reports | Customer comms, duplicate pitches |

## Payment & Billing
- **Stripe** = primary rail (website automations handle monthly + one-time)
- Contract ref: `FLA-YYYY-###` on Stripe metadata + GHL `fla_contract_ref`
- Square = legacy only

## GHL Stage Triggers (Automatic — Do Not Duplicate)
Stage change inside GHL fires workflows. Cursor sets stage ONLY:
- New Lead → wf_01_capture
- Qualified → wf_02_qualify
- Proposal Sent → wf_03_proposal
- Contract Signed → wf_04_onboard

**Never call `campaign`/workflow enrollment via Zapier for customer/prospect workflows.** Exception: internal `War Room SMS Alert` workflow only.

## Idempotency Tags (Check Before Every Write)
`comet_intake`, `perplexity_scored`, `ghl_wf_active`, `cursor_stage_set`, `fulfillment_complete`, `pitch_ready`

## Client Record Completeness
Load `config/client-record-schema.json`. No stage advance without required fields.

## Proposal Standard (Gold)
Load `config/proposal-template-canonical.json` before any pitch.
- Template: `templates/proposals/reliable-roofer-dedicated.html`
- 6-slide dedicated HTML deck with ROI modeling — not generic PDF
- Docs: `docs/deal-machine/PROPOSAL-TEMPLATE.md`

## Production Skills
- **`deal-hunter`** — B2B lead gen (discover → enrich → GHL intake → qualify → pitch top 5)
- **`deal-orchestrator`** — audit, gap-fill, Stripe verify, close detect, digest

Load `config/lead-gen-config.json` before every hunt run.

## Slack Routing
- **#war-room** (`C0BDLF5JUQ4`) — **ALL agent Slack posts. Monster sales hype. 5+ posts per run. @mention Jonathan + Heaven. NO DMs. NO sold-clients.**
- **#sold-clients** — humans only; agents post closes in war-room with 🏆
- **#project-update** — engineering only — never deal ops

## Zapier MCP Scope
Load `config/zapier-war-room.json`. Zapier focuses on **#war-room only** for deal ops.

| Zapier DOES | Zapier DOES NOT |
|-------------|-----------------|
| Post to `#war-room` | Post to `#project-update` |
| GHL lead intake + idempotent upserts | Enroll **customer** GHL workflows (`campaign`) |
| Deal Hunter Apollo enrich + GHL writes | Customer SMS/email |
| GHL SMS (internal War Room workflow enrollment only) | Duplicate lead intake |
| Stripe verify via Stripe MCP | Browser automation (Comet fallback only) |
| War Room monster hype in `#war-room` only (@mention leaders) | Slack DMs, #sold-clients, #project-update |

## SMS Alerts (War Room)
Load `config/war-room-alerts.json`. Critical events SMS **Jonathan + Heaven** via **GHL only**:
- Set contact `notes` then enroll in `War Room SMS Alert` workflow via Zapier `campaign` (internal only — see `docs/deal-machine/SMS-SETUP.md`)
- Workflow must exist in GHL first — Comet handoff: `docs/deal-machine/SMS-COMET-HANDOFF.md`
- RingCentral is NOT used for texting
- Always post Slack `#war-room` even if GHL SMS fails
